---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="QSol Analytics cookie policy. Information about cookies and tracking on our website."
>
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-light"><strong>Last updated:</strong> February 2024</p>

      <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit websites. They're commonly used for website functionality, analytics, and advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We prioritise your privacy.</strong> We use Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly analytics service that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Does not use cookies</li>
        <li>Does not collect personal data</li>
        <li>Does not track you across websites</li>
        <li>Is fully GDPR compliant without requiring consent</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>
      <p>
        Currently, our website does not set any cookies. If this changes (for example, if we add functionality that requires cookies), we will update this policy and implement appropriate consent mechanisms.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Some third-party services embedded on our site may set their own cookies:
      </p>

      <h3>Calendly (Booking Widget)</h3>
      <p>
        If you use our booking widget, Calendly may set cookies to enable scheduling functionality. See <a href="https://calendly.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Calendly's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Formspree (Contact Form)</h3>
      <p>
        Our contact form is processed by Formspree, which may use minimal technical cookies. See <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Formspree's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can control cookies through your browser settings. Since we don't use tracking cookies, no cookie consent banner is required on our site.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our cookie practices, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@qsol-analytics.com">hello@qsol-analytics.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
